<item>
            <title>[LU-18469] Activate/De-activate individual nodemaps</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18469</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It could be desirable to be able to de-activate a nodemap and later re-activate it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;De-activating would mean the nodemap definition is kept, but new client mount attempts would fail.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To implement this, it is possible to add a new nodemap property such as &apos;inactive&apos;. A storage administrator can then set  &apos;nodemap.nm0.inactive=1&apos; to deactivate a nodemap, after which all new mount attempts for that nodemap will fail.&lt;br/&gt;
Similarly &apos;inactive=0&apos; would reactivate the nodemap.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
