                            <comment id="446166" author="gerrit" created="Fri, 28 Feb 2025 08:11:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Oleg Drokin &amp;lt;green@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; merged in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/57096/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/57096/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18469&quot; title=&quot;Activate/De-activate individual nodemaps&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18469&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18469&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; ptlrpc: Add flag to deny mounts for nodemaps&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: &lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 4ced247208624eb56c4e1ed23cacd31947883f34&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="436585" author="sebastien" created="Tue, 26 Nov 2024 10:00:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, you are right, &quot;deny_mount&quot; is just fine, and works well for the default nodemap as well, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="436452" author="JIRAUSER19288" created="Mon, 25 Nov 2024 16:42:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Possible, though we already have another property, &quot;readonly_mount&quot;, which only applies to new mounts as well. I would drop the &quot;new&quot; to keep it short and consistent with the other properties. Nevertheless, I don&apos;t have a strong opinion here, so if you&apos;d prefer &quot;deny_new_mounts&quot;, we can use this. It is definitely descriptive enough.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="436446" author="sebastien" created="Mon, 25 Nov 2024 16:02:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What about &quot;deny_new_mounts&quot;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="436441" author="JIRAUSER19288" created="Mon, 25 Nov 2024 15:29:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sebastien&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sebastien&quot;&gt;sebastien&lt;/a&gt; as this topic came up in Gerrit that &quot;inactive&quot; may not be an appropriate property name because intuitively it could be understood as temporarily disabling all individual nodemap settings to defaults (similar as &quot;lctl nodemap_activate 0&quot; would work for global). Instead only new mounting attempts are denied by this setting.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Perhaps the property name &quot;deny_mount&quot; or &quot;&lt;del&gt;deny_all&lt;/del&gt;&quot; would be more suitable (which would be consistent to the existing &quot;deny_unknown&quot; property)?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(edit) Since &quot;deny_unknown&quot; denies access even on existing clients, &quot;deny_all&quot; only working during mount would be inconsistent.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="436042" author="gerrit" created="Thu, 21 Nov 2024 13:03:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Marc Vef &amp;lt;mvef@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/57096&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/57096&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
